WebFlux Controller Style (Annotated)
    @RestController
    @RequestMapping("/api/orders")
    public class OrderReactiveController {
    
        private final OrderReactiveService orderService;
    
        @GetMapping
        public Flux<Order> getAllOrders() {           // returns stream of orders
            return orderService.findAll();
        }
    
        @GetMapping("/{id}")
        public Mono<Order> getOrder(@PathVariable Long id) {  // 0 or 1 order
            return orderService.findById(id)
                .switchIfEmpty(Mono.error(
                    new OrderNotFoundException(id)));
        }
    
        @PostMapping
        @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.CREATED)
        public Mono<Order> createOrder(@RequestBody @Valid Mono<Order> order) {
            return order.flatMap(orderService::save);
        }
    
        @DeleteMapping("/{id}")
        @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.NO_CONTENT)
        public Mono<Void> deleteOrder(@PathVariable Long id) {
            return orderService.delete(id);
        }
    
        // ── Server-Sent Events streaming ─────────────────────────
        @GetMapping(value = "/stream",
                    produces = MediaType.TEXT_EVENT_STREAM_VALUE)
        public Flux<Order> streamOrders() {
            return orderService.findAll()
                .delayElements(Duration.ofMillis(500));  // stream with delay
        }
    }

WebFlux Functional Router Style:
  // Handler — replaces controller methods
  @Component
  public class OrderHandler {
  
      private final OrderReactiveService orderService;
  
      public Mono<ServerResponse> findAll(ServerRequest request) {
          return ServerResponse.ok()
              .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)
              .body(orderService.findAll(), Order.class);
      }
  
      public Mono<ServerResponse> findById(ServerRequest request) {
          Long id = Long.valueOf(request.pathVariable("id"));
          return orderService.findById(id)
              .flatMap(order -> ServerResponse.ok().bodyValue(order))
              .switchIfEmpty(ServerResponse.notFound().build());
      }
  
      public Mono<ServerResponse> create(ServerRequest request) {
          return request.bodyToMono(Order.class)
              .flatMap(orderService::save)
              .flatMap(saved -> ServerResponse
                  .created(URI.create("/api/orders/" + saved.getId()))
                  .bodyValue(saved));
      }
  }

// Router — maps URLs to handler methods
    @Configuration
    public class OrderRouter {
    
        @Bean
        public RouterFunction<ServerResponse> orderRoutes(OrderHandler handler) {
            return RouterFunctions.route()
                .GET("/api/orders",       handler::findAll)
                .GET("/api/orders/{id}",  handler::findById)
                .POST("/api/orders",      handler::create)
                .DELETE("/api/orders/{id}", handler::delete)
                .build();
        }
    }
Reactive Service with R2DBC
    @Service
    public class OrderReactiveService {
    
        private final OrderR2dbcRepository orderRepo;
    
        // Mono operators — transform, filter, compose
        public Mono<Order> findById(Long id) {
            return orderRepo.findById(id)
                .map(this::enrichWithDefaults)      // transform
                .filter(o -> o.getAmount() > 0)     // filter
                .doOnNext(o -> log.info("Found: {}", o))  // side effect
                .onErrorMap(ex ->                   // translate exception
                    new OrderNotFoundException(id));
        }
    
        // Flux operators — stream of items
        public Flux<Order> findAllPending() {
            return orderRepo.findByStatus("PENDING")
                .filter(o -> o.getAmount() > 100)
                .map(this::applyDiscount)
                .take(50)                           // limit to 50
                .doOnComplete(() -> log.info("Done streaming"));
        }
    
        // Combining multiple reactive sources
        public Mono<OrderSummary> getOrderSummary(Long id) {
            Mono<Order> orderMono = orderRepo.findById(id);
            Mono<Customer> customerMono = customerRepo.findByOrderId(id);
    
            return Mono.zip(orderMono, customerMono,   // combine two Monos
                (order, customer) -> OrderSummary.builder()
                    .order(order)
                    .customer(customer)
                    .build());
        }
    
        // Error handling
        public Mono<Order> saveWithRetry(Order order) {
            return orderRepo.save(order)
                .retryWhen(Retry.backoff(3, Duration.ofMillis(100)))
                .onErrorResume(ex -> {              // fallback on failure
                    log.error("Save failed", ex);
                    return Mono.error(new OrderSaveException(ex));
                });
        }
    }

WebFlux Testing with WebTestClient
    @SpringBootTest(webEnvironment = SpringBootTest.WebEnvironment.RANDOM_PORT)
    class OrderReactiveControllerTest {
    
        @Autowired
        private WebTestClient webTestClient;    // reactive alternative to MockMvc
    
        @Test
        void getOrder_shouldReturn200() {
            webTestClient.get()
                .uri("/api/orders/1")
                .accept(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)
                .exchange()
                .expectStatus().isOk()
                .expectBody(Order.class)
                .value(order -> {
                    assertThat(order.getId()).isEqualTo(1L);
                    assertThat(order.getAmount()).isPositive();
                });
        }
    
        @Test
        void getAllOrders_shouldReturnFlux() {
            webTestClient.get()
                .uri("/api/orders")
                .exchange()
                .expectStatus().isOk()
                .expectBodyList(Order.class)
                .hasSize(3);
        }
    
        @Test
        void streamOrders_shouldReceiveEvents() {
            webTestClient.get()
                .uri("/api/orders/stream")
                .accept(MediaType.TEXT_EVENT_STREAM)
                .exchange()
                .expectStatus().isOk()
                .returnResult(Order.class)
                .getResponseBody()
                .take(5)                         // take first 5 events
                .as(StepVerifier::create)
                .expectNextCount(5)
                .verifyComplete();
        }
    }

Reactive Operators — Quick Reference:
  TRANSFORM
  ──────────
  .map(item -> transform(item))            sync 1-to-1 transform
  .flatMap(item -> asyncOp(item))          async 1-to-1 (non-blocking)
  .flatMapMany(item -> flux)               Mono → Flux expansion
  .concatMap(item -> asyncOp(item))        flatMap but preserves order

  FILTER
  ───────
  .filter(item -> condition)               keep matching items
  .take(n)                                 first N items only
  .skip(n)                                 skip first N items
  .distinct()                              remove duplicates
  .limitRate(n)                            backpressure control

  COMBINE
  ────────
  Mono.zip(monoA, monoB, (a,b) -> ...)    combine two Monos
  Flux.merge(fluxA, fluxB)                merge two Fluxes (interleaved)
  Flux.concat(fluxA, fluxB)               fluxA completes, then fluxB
  Flux.zip(fluxA, fluxB)                  pair items by position

  ERROR HANDLING
  ───────────────
      .onErrorReturn(fallback)                 return fallback on error
      .onErrorResume(ex -> Mono.just(x))       switch to fallback Mono/Flux
      .onErrorMap(ex -> new CustomEx(ex))      translate exception type
      .retry(3)                                retry up to 3 times
      .retryWhen(Retry.backoff(3, ofMillis(100))) exponential backoff retry
      .timeout(Duration.ofSeconds(5))          fail if no item within 5s

  SIDE EFFECTS (no data change)
  ──────────────────────────────
    .doOnNext(item -> log(item))             on each item
    .doOnError(ex -> alert(ex))              on error
    .doOnComplete(() -> notify())            on stream completion
    .doFinally(signal -> cleanup())          always — like finally

Complete Architecture — MVC + WebFlux Side by Side

  SPRING MVC STACK
  ─────────────────
  Client
    │ HTTP Request
    ▼
  Tomcat (thread pool — 200 threads default)
    │ assigns Thread-N to this request
    ▼
  DispatcherServlet
    │
    ▼
  HandlerMapping → finds @GetMapping method
    │
    ▼
  HandlerInterceptor.preHandle()
    │
    ▼
  @RestController method
    │ thread BLOCKS here waiting for DB
    ▼
  Service → Repository → JDBC → DB (blocking)
    │ thread unblocks, has result
    ▼
  Jackson serializes to JSON
    │
    ▼
  Response written — thread returned to pool
    │
    ▼
  Client receives response


  SPRING WEBFLUX STACK
  ─────────────────────
  Client
    │ HTTP Request
    ▼
  Netty (event loop — 8 threads for 8 cores)
    │ EventLoop-1 receives request, does NOT block
    ▼
  DispatcherHandler (reactive equivalent)
    │
    ▼
  HandlerMapping → finds handler
    │
    ▼
  WebFilter chain (reactive filter)
    │
    ▼
  @RestController / RouterFunction
    │ returns Mono/Flux — subscription deferred
    ▼
  R2DBC non-blocking DB call
    │ EventLoop-1 FREE to handle other requests
    │ ...handles 50 other requests meanwhile...
    │ DB responds → EventLoop-1 picks up signal
    ▼
  Reactor assembles result
    │
    ▼
  Jackson serializes reactively
    │
    ▼
  Client receives response

Best Practice:
Never block in WebFlux — no Thread.sleep(), no .block(), no JDBC calls — use R2DBC
Use WebFlux functional style for complex routing logic — annotated style for simple CRUD
Choose MVC if you use JPA/JDBC — WebFlux + blocking drivers defeats the purpose entirely

